		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>most convenient way to convert NSF to wav?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Yes, I know you can easily record a wav from an nsf from some of the main emulators; but what I'd like is to take an nsf and have it rip every individual track, loop it a certain number of times, fade out and stick it into a wav for each track. In short, I want to automate the process of creating my own burnt CDs of NSF =)  
<br />
<br />I figured if there are any modern NSF playing plugins I could probably use whatever media player's built in functionality to convert nsfs straight to the format of my choice.
<br />
<br />Failing that, I thought perhaps I could actually use lua scripting with one of the FCEUX emulators to tell it when to start and stop recording wavs..but I'm not sure if they expose bindings to all parts of the interface or what all you can do with it.
<br />
<br />Ideas?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


