	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I used to use Winamp to do it (selecting the diskwriter plugin for output).  If there was a playlist that did what you want, that would be a really fast way to do it.
<br />
<br />I remember loop point detection being discussed here before, I don't remember what the conclusion was exactly, but it seems like it would be tricky to detect.
<br />
<br />But then if the playlist doesn't do fade-outs and such, I'm sure there must be a decent audio program that can apply the same effect to several .WAV files all at once.

		

		</td>
